  "prompt": "If somebody is smoking weed around me, is it possible to get high off of second hand smoke?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to get high from secondhand marijuana smoke, although the likelihood and intensity can vary based on several factors, such as the amount of smoke, the ventilation of the area, and your own sensitivity to THC (the psychoactive component in cannabis). In a well-ventilated area, the chances of experiencing noticeable effects from secondhand smoke are lower. However, in a confined space with significant exposure to secondhand smoke, it is more likely that some THC could enter your system. Keep in mind that individual responses to cannabis can vary widely. If you're concerned about the effects of secondhand smoke, it's best to avoid areas where people are smoking.",
